MCPConnectorEnabledDesc=Enables the module REST endpoints. Keep it disabled until setup and tests are complete.
MCPConnectorReadOnlyDesc=Indicates that the connector only reads data. In V1 this option is enforced and cannot be disabled.
MCPConnectorDolibarrBaseUrlDesc=Public address of your Dolibarr instance, for example https://erp.example.com. Used for links and generated files.
MCPConnectorDolibarrApiUrlDesc=Full Dolibarr REST API address, usually https://erp.example.com/api/index.php.
MCPConnectorApiUserDesc=Technical user used by the MCP server. It should only have the required read permissions.
MCPConnectorApiKeyDesc=API key of the technical Dolibarr user. Enter it only to save or replace the stored key.
MCPConnectorEntityModeDesc=Defines which entity is used for MCP calls. In V1, prefer the current entity of the API user.
MCPConnectorPublicUrlDesc=Public HTTPS URL of the MCP server to configure in ChatGPT, for example https://mcp.example.com/mcp.
MCPConnectorNodePortDesc=Local port where the Node.js application listens behind Apache or Nginx.
MCPConnectorAllowedToolsDesc=Select only the tools ChatGPT may call. Powerplant PV tools are available only when the module is detected.
MCPConnectorLogEnabledDesc=Stores MCP calls for audit and diagnostics, without logging the API key.
MCPConnectorLogRetentionDaysDesc=Number of days to keep logs before manual purge from the MCP logs page.
